snippet.textDisplay:
As a asian, i understand why mushu doesnt appear in the movie. First of all, we must respect chinese belief about dragon. Dragon isnt something you can make fun, being comedian in the movie. In western culture, its fine to make "god" as funny things (as long as its for joke), but you cant do that in asian culture. We must respect A LOT OF THINGS.

In western culture, you can call your older sibling with his/her name, but in asian culture you do not allowed to call your older sibling with his/her name. Theres always a honor call to everyone, include someone whom younger. Dare to call older people with his/her name, then you will get punishment from your parents. Dare to make fun about god, then you wont try to see your parents face. Just imagine it, it would be horrible for every asian child 😂😂😂

Yes its so outdated, but its our identity as asian. Thats our culture, our blood. Please, respect it. 😉😉
